Word of warning: Take care with those filings. I once swept a pile of brass filings off a countertop without thinking, and got them in my hand. Which means every time I put pressure on them, they'd stab me a little. It was kind of cool, because they started out more or less invisible (the color matched my skin closely enough that you couldn't see it), but as they oxidized inside my body they became progressively darker. Eventually they worked their way out as my skin aged and sloughed off (natural process, but sounds horrific any way you describe it).

Also, I learned that brass is not strongly effected by an MRI magnet. Came up when I broke my leg in an unrelated incident while the filings were still in my hand.
